K9Copy (A Linux DVD Shrink)

k9copy is DVD backup utility which allow the copy of one or more
titles from a DVD9 to a DVD5. The DVD video stream is compressed
by the program Vamps.

Homepage: http://k9copy.sourceforge.net/

K9Copy requires the following dependencies to build:
DVDAuthor, libdvdread or libdvdnav, and mencoder/mplayer
for which buildscripts are available at http://www.slackbuilds.org

NOTE: mencoder is part of mplayer.
NOTE: libdvdread and libdvdnav conflict DO NOT INSTALL BOTH.